On Tue, 24 Sep 2002, Andrew Mueller wrote:

> OK, now I have the bentley and haynes manual and find
> no mention of the pilot bearing.  is it called the
> pinion in the bentley?  sounds like i should just go
> ahead and try to find the thing myself

The pilot bearing lives in the end of the crankshaft in the middle of the
flywheel.  The pilot shaft extending from the transmission runs in this
bearing.

George Lyle

